Making leathercraft accessible for all!

One day while searching for a new wallet, I came across a video of someone making their own on YouTube. I was instantly hooked after seeing the process and tools leathercrafters use to make their products, probably watching 100 videos in the process. There was only one problem: I live in a small apartment and didn’t have the space for a fully decked out studio filled with machines and tools. It was a struggle to find someone on YouTube who was working with the same space restrictions but I was determined to find a way to be a leathercrafter. Today, I have the same small apartment but have turned it into an effective space to make leather products. My goal is to help beginners and small space crafters alike to show that it is possible to turn any space into a leather working shop.

Hi! I'm Jeremiah and I aim to share the juggling arts with the world. I work primarily as an entertainer, but love teaching people to juggle and flow. The real power behind these arts is in the experience of learning to do it yourself. No one is born with the ability, but almost everyone can learn!
